---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <style>
      .hero {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 4rem 1rem 3rem;
      }
      .hero h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      .hero p {
        max-width: 650px;
        margin: 0 auto 2rem;
        color: rgb(var(--gray));
        font-size: 1.15rem;
      }
      .nav-cards {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
        gap: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 960px;
        margin: 2rem auto 0;
        padding: 0 1rem;
      }
      .card {
        background: white;
        border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray-light), 1);
        border-radius: 14px;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: inherit;
        transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
      }
      .card:hover {
        box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
        transform: translateY(-2px);
      }
      /* Colour bar at top of each card */
      .card::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
        height: 4px;
        border-radius: 14px 14px 0 0;
      }
      .card-part1::before { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #1a6ea3, #2389c8); }
      .card-part2::before { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #0d7a6b, #16a88f); }
      .card-part3::before { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #c47c1a, #e8b96a); }
      .card-conclusion::before { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #a78bfa); }

      .card-label {
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
      }
      /* Each label colour matches its bar */
      .card-part1 .card-label       { color: #1a6ea3; }
      .card-part2 .card-label       { color: #0d7a6b; }
      .card-part3 .card-label       { color: #c47c1a; }
      .card-conclusion .card-label  { color: #7c3aed; }

      .card h2 {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
        /* Reset any global h2 styles from global.css */
        border: none !important;
        padding: 0 !important;
        border-left: none !important;
        color: #111827;
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.3;
      }
      .card p {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        /* High-contrast muted — dark enough to read on white */
        color: #374151;
        margin: 0;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <h1>Auditable AI in Fintech</h1>
        <p>
          How algorithmic systems, compliance automation, and the recursive compliance dynamic
          are reshaping Anti-Money Laundering and financial fraud detection.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="nav-cards">
        <a href="/blog/part-1-domain" class="card card-part1">
          <div class="card-label">Part 1</div>
          <h2>The Domain &amp; Challenges</h2>
          <p>Why rule-based heuristics collapse against adaptive adversaries, and the asymmetric cost of misclassification.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/blog/part-2-ml-technologies" class="card card-part2">
          <div class="card-label">Part 2</div>
          <h2>ML Architectures</h2>
          <p>Graph Neural Networks, Heterogeneous Graph Transformers, VAEs, and Isolation Forests.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/blog/part-3-ethical-implications" class="card card-part3">
          <div class="card-label">Part 3</div>
          <h2>Ethical Governance</h2>
          <p>Rudin's challenge, fairness impossibility theorems, and the EU AI Act's auditable inference demand.</p>
        </a>

        <a href="/blog/conclusion" class="card card-conclusion">
          <div class="card-label">Conclusion</div>
          <h2>The Asymmetry That Will Define the Next Decade</h2>
          <p>The Recursive Compliance Dynamic as a permanent condition, and what it means for regulators and institutions alike.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
